<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7442] Parallelize unit test runner</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7442</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we spend ~15 minutes running unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can parallelize the unit tests by splitting the classes up across processes and using more cores.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch adds a new variable -Dtest.runners=X (default is 1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running with 4 runtime goes from 15min to 6min. &lt;br/&gt;
Beyond 1 runner per core I don&apos;t see much of a difference&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
